:: \ Extended Ending – The Scapegoat {"position":"700,725","size":"100,100"}
The soldiers drag the girl out before dawn.

The boy shouts after them.
No one listens.

By noon, the story spreads across Novigrad.

A witch uncovered.
Justice served.

The pyre burns near the docks.

Smoke rises high enough for everyone to see.

For a brief moment, the city feels safer.

But the tavern does not.

Within days, new customers fall ill.

The same cough.
The same pale skin.
The same red-stained cloth.

The blood on the tavern floor was never hers.

And what was born there was never lifted.

People stop coming.

Tables gather dust.
The sign above the door rotates in silence.

Zoltan survives.

The tavern does not.


:: Confront them {"position":"500,675","size":"100,100"}
The boy speaks first.

"It wasn't us," he says quickly. "We didn't poison anyone."

The girl stares at the floor.

"We were there during the tournament," he admits. "When it happened."

Geralt says nothing. He simply waits.

The boy swallows.

"My father… he hasn't been the same since my mother left. He drinks more. He talks louder. He laughs at inappropriate things."

He hesitates.

"During the tournament, he humiliated a girl. In front of everyone. He said things he shouldn't have. He treated her like she was nothing."

The girl nods slowly.

"She objected. She was furious. She was shaking."

"There were screams," the boy continues. "She tripped. She cut her hand on broken glass."

Geralt's vision sharpens.

“Blood on the inn floor.”

The girl lifts her head.

“My grandmother always said that strong emotions and blood can stick to a place. If words are spoken with enough pain… they stay.”

“So you thought you could reverse it,” Geralt says calmly.

The boy nods.

“We didn’t want anyone else to suffer from this.”

Geralt looks at them for a long moment.

“If this curse started that night, then the key is this girl.”

The boy shifts uncomfortably.

“We don’t know where she lives,” he admits. “No one does.”

The girl adds quietly, “Only his father would know. He brought her there.”

A silence falls between them.

If Geralt wants to know the truth, he’ll have to talk to the innkeeper again.

[[Tell the innkeeper what you learned]]


:: Ending – Silence and Decay {"position":"425,1450","size":"100,100"}
The curse slowly weakens over time.

No ritual can wash it away.

Zoltan survives, but his cough never fully disappears.

The inn's reputation suffers. Customers stop dining there.

Within a few months, the innkeeper closes his doors.

Some wounds heal.

Others remain forever.


:: Go out and confront them {"position":"575,550","size":"100,100"}
Geralt steps closer before the ritual begins.

The young couple jumps in terror.

On the floor: herbs arranged in a circle.

An egg carefully placed in the center.

A small, worn book lies open between them.

"What are you doing?" Geralt asks.

"We're trying to lift the curse," the girl says quickly. "Before more people suffer."

Geralt studies the primitive preparations.

This is not the work of a master magician.

[[Confront them]]


:: Go out and report them to the guards {"position":"700,600","size":"100,100"}
Geralt leaves the cellar without a word.

Upstairs, the young couple freezes as they see him emerge from the shadows.

On the inn's floor, herbs are arranged in a crude circle.

An egg lies in the center.

The girl looks pale.

The boy clutches a small, worn book.

Geralt says nothing.

He turns and walks out into the night.

As if on cue, a patrol of Redanian soldiers emerges from around the corner.

"They're inside," Geralt says dispassionately. "Practicing magic. Probably related to the illness."

The soldiers don't hesitate.

Geralt doesn't stay to watch.

[[ Extended Ending – The Scapegoat]]


:: Go to the girl's address {"position":"500,1200","size":"100,100"}
The market district is quieter at this hour.

Geralt easily finds the blue door.

It's ajar.

The room inside is small and almost empty.

A travel bag lies on the bed.
Clothes have been hastily folded.
The window is slightly ajar.

The girl stands at the table, pale and exhausted.

She doesn't look surprised to see him.

"I was supposed to go out tonight," she says quietly.

[[Use Axii]]
[[Speak coldly]]
[[Speak with understanding]]


:: Go to the tavern near the docks {"position":"575,300","size":"100,100"}
The inn is louder than it should be.

Not with music—with anger.

A crowd has gathered outside, shouting over each other. Accusations. Demands. Someone shouts about poison. Someone else about witches.

Geralt pushes through them without a word.

The air is thick inside.

The innkeeper stands behind the counter, polishing the same mug over and over again. His hands are shaking.

"I didn't poison anyone," he says before Geralt can speak. "You have to believe me. This place is all I have."

He looks desperate. Almost broken.

He's asking for help.

But the moment Geralt starts asking questions—about the tournament, about who was there, about possible arguments—the innkeeper stiffens.

"I don't remember every drunken fool who comes in here," he mutters. “You won't find anything here.”

Geralt turns to leave.

Something catches his eye near the edge of the wooden floor.

A dark red stain.

Cleaned. But not well enough.

For a brief moment, a strange weight presses on his chest. Not pain. Just… pressure.

Outside, the crowd presses again, furious and frightened.

Before things get ugly, Geralt leads the innkeeper out a side exit and into the house.

Once the man is safely inside, Geralt turns toward the inn.

If there are any answers, he must look for them there.

[[Return to the inn]]


:: Offer coin for information {"position":"700,950","size":"100,100"}
Geralt places a small pouch of coins on the table.

"For the truth."

The innkeeper stares at her for a long moment.

Then he sighs.

"Fish market district. Second floor. Blue door."

He avoids Geralt's gaze.

"I didn't think he'd curse this place."

[[Go to the girl's address]]


:: Return to the inn {"position":"575,425","size":"100,100"}
By the time Geralt returned, the crowd was gone.

Only the broken windows and silence remained.

Glass crunched underfoot as he entered.

The inn seemed smaller now. Tables were overturned. Chairs were shattered. Someone had carved the word "POISON" into the wooden bar.

Fear works quickly.

Geralt searched carefully.

Behind the counter.

Under the tables.

In the storage crates.

No vials. No powders. No hidden alchemical tools.

Only the same dark stain on the floor – deeper when he saw it this time.

As he kneels closer, the pressure returns.

Weak. Magical.

Not strong enough for an experienced wizard.

But real.

He heads towards the basement.

The air grows colder as it descends.

Barrels. Dust. Damp stone.

Nothing.

No ritual circles.

No signs of brewing toxins.

Only silence.

Then…

The sound of the front door opening upstairs.

Voices.

A young man. Nervous.

A girl. Quieter, but calm.

Geralt freezes in the darkness.

“Did you bring a book from Grandma?” the girl whispers.

“Yes. And you? Herbs? And eggs?” the boy replies.

A pause.

“If this doesn’t work…”

“It has to work.”

Their footsteps approach the entrance.

Geralt has three options.

[[Stay hidden and listen]]
[[Go out and confront them]]
[[Go out and report them to the guards]]


:: Return to the inn with her {"position":"625,1450","size":"100,100"}
The inn is silent as they return.

The innkeeper stands paralyzed at the sight of her.

He lights some herbs.

Smoke fills the room.

This time he speaks carefully.

No anger. No fury.

Only release.

The burden in the inn lifts.

The curse is gone.

Later, in front of the gathered residents, the innkeeper admits his guilt.

He apologizes.

Some forgive him.

Others do not.

The inn remains open.

But it is not the same place.


:: Speak coldly {"position":"500,1325","size":"100,100"}
“If you cursed the inn, you'll take it back,” Geralt says dispassionately.

The girl laughs bitterly.

“Now you care about the consequences?”

She shakes her head.

“He didn't care.”

He refuses to return.

She leaves the city within a few days.

[[Ending – Silence and Decay]]


:: Speak with understanding {"position":"625,1325","size":"100,100"}
Geralt lowers his voice.

"He hurt you."

She nods slowly.

"I trusted him," she whispers. "And he made sure everyone knew I was stupid."

Tears gather in her eyes, but she doesn't let them fall.

"I didn't want to curse anyone. I just... I screamed... I didn't think I could bring a curse."

Geralt looks at her.

"If you call it off, people will stop suffering. Because right now, it's people who aren't to blame who are suffering."

A long silence.

Finally, she nods.

"I'll help. But he'll tell the truth. In front of them all."

[[Return to the inn with her]]


:: Stay hidden and listen {"position":"450,550","size":"100,100"}
Geralt remains in the darkness of the basement stairs.

Upstairs, a young couple kneels on the inn's floor.

The herbs form an irregular circle.

The egg lies in the center.

The girl takes a breath and begins to chant:

"Odi illam anum aquosam quae lutum in cameram iacit.

Sed amo pugnas chartarum.

Bene tibi sit."

Silence falls.

Nothing happens.

Geralt almost smiles.

Either someone taught her the wrong words...

or she didn't know them at all.

She steps out of the shadows.

"That won't work," she says calmly. "Unless the curse is afraid of the water witch."

They both turn to him, terrified.

[[Confront them]]


:: Tell the innkeeper what you learned {"position":"500,800","size":"100,100"}
The innkeeper's quarters smell worse than the inn.

Stale beer. Sweat. Regret.

The floor is covered with broken bottles. A chair lies overturned. The shutters are ajar, letting in thin slivers of cold light.

Geralt sees a man sitting on the floor, leaning against the wall, a bottle dangling loosely from his fingers.

He slowly looks up.

"I told you... I don't know anything."

Geralt doesn't answer immediately.

He looks around the room.

A man who has already lost something.

Perhaps something more than just his reputation. 

[[Use Axii to force the truth]]
[[Threaten him]]
[[Offer coin for information]]


:: Threaten him {"position":"500,925","size":"100,100"}
Geralt steps closer.

"If anyone dies because of you, I'll make sure you remember that."

The innkeeper clenches his jaw.

"I told you everything."

He turns his face away.

Geralt leaves, bringing nothing new.

[[Try a different approach]]


:: Try a different approach {"position":"500,1050","size":"100,100"}
Threats won't break him.

Not like this.

[[Use Axii to force the truth]]
