:: Untitled Passage {"position":"575,175","size":"100,100"}
Novigrad never smelled clean.

Salt from the sea mixed with smoke from the chimneys, but today something else lingered in the air — tension.

People were quieter. Watching. Whispering.

Geralt didn’t need rumors to know something was wrong.

He found Zoltan in one of the city wards, sitting upright only because pride wouldn’t let him lie down.

"You picked a bad time to visit," the dwarf rasped, pressing a stained cloth to his mouth. "Feels like I swallowed broken glass."

Blood. Not much. But enough.

Around him, others looked the same — pale, sweating, eyes red from strain. Not drunk. Not poisoned. Something else.

They had nothing in common.

Except one thing.

Each of them had spent the previous evening at a tavern near the docks.
A place known for cheap ale and loud gwent tournaments.

And now the city was starting to talk.

Poison.
Curses.
Czarownice.

Geralt exhaled slowly.

If this turned into panic, someone would end up burning for it.

[[Go to the tavern near the docks]]


:: Use Axii {"position":"375,1325","size":"100,100"}
Geralt's eyes flashed faintly.

"Tell me what happened."

Her shoulders stiffen. Her voice becomes distant.

She explains the argument.

Humiliation.

Blood.

Words she spoke in anger.

When the effect wears off, she steps back.

"You had no right."

Her expression hardens.

"I can't fix this. Let him live with it."

By morning, she disappears from Novigrad.

[[Ending – Silence and Decay]]


:: Use Axii to force the truth {"position":"300,950","size":"100,100"}
Geralt's eyes twinkled slightly.

"Look at me," he said quietly.

The innkeeper's resistance weakened.

"She lived near the fish market," he murmured. "A small, rented room. Second floor. Blue door."

His voice trembled.

"I didn't want it to go this far."

[[Go to the girl's address]]
